-- Saudi Trade Ministry Files Cases Against Nadec, Eqtisadiah Says
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-07-25T11:07:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/saudi-trade-ministry-files-cases-against-nadec-eqtisadiah-says.html
Saudi Arabia ’s Ministry of Trade and
Industry filed three legal cases against  National Agriculture
Development Co. (NADEC) , the country’s biggest food producer,  al-
Eqtisadiah  reported, citing a person at the ministry whom it
didn’t name.  The ministry filed the cases with the Bureau of
Investigation and Public Prosecution after three violations
related to production dates on dairy products and juices, the
newspaper said.  The ministry seized 100,000 bottles of the products
yesterday, al-Eqtisadiah said.  The public relations department at the company, known as
Nadec, declined to comment when contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Manama   wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maher Chmaytelli at   mchmaytelli@bloomberg.net  